  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EmptySet
    The Axiom of Existence: There exists a set {} that contains no elements; furthermore, this set is unique.
    Intersection  
    OrderedPair
    Ordered Pair definition: For all sets a and b, define OrderedPair(a,b) as new Pair(new Singleton(a), new Pair(a,b)).
    Pair
    The Axiom of Pair: Given two sets x and y, there exists a set {x,y} that contains exactly them both.
    Powerset
    The Axiom of Power:
    Set
    A set is that which may contain elements; these elements, in turn, are also sets.
    Singleton
    Singleton Theorem: For every set x, there exists a set that contains exactly x.
    Subset
    The Axiom of Specification: For every set x, and a proposition p, there exists a set y such that: for all sets t, if t is an element of y then t is an element of x and p(t) is true.
